closer to identifying
the suspect.

01:14.808 --> 01:18.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's the clearest look yet at
the alleged
gunman who attacked the Reina
club early New

01:18.845 --> 01:20.347 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Year's morning.

01:20.380 --> 01:24.151 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Turkish officials say he rained
bullets and
explosives on holiday revelers.

01:24.184 --> 01:26.820 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The deputy prime minister said
the investigation
is progressing.

01:26.853 --> 01:29.923 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NUMAN KURTULMUS, Turkish Deputy
Prime Minister
(through translator):
Information about the

01:29.957 --> 01:33.694 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
fingerprints and basic
appearance of the terrorist
have been found.

01:33.727 --> 01:37.664 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We hope that we will find not
only the terrorist,
but also his connections and
those who gave

01:37.698 --> 01:39.967 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
him support inside and outside
the club.

01:40.000 --> 01:43.904 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Hours earlier,
the Islamic
State group claimed
responsibility, and called

01:43.937 --> 01:46.940 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the gunman a heroic soldier of
the caliphate.

01:46.974 --> 01:51.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The statement said: "The blood
of Muslims
that is being shed by Turkey's
airstrikes

01:51.411 --> 01:57.417 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and artillery shelling will turn
into fire
on its territories."

01:57.451 --> 02:02.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Turkey has been a key member of
the air campaign
against ISIS and has sent troops
into Syria

02:02.122 --> 02:04.124 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in part to fight the group.

02:04.157 --> 02:08.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still, Turkey's military vowed
to continue
strikes on Islamic State
fighters.

02:08.495 --> 02:13.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it released new footage of
air raids on
ISIS positions in Syria.

02:13.533 --> 02:19.406 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Meanwhile, in Istanbul,
survivors of the nightclub
attack painted a more detailed
picture of

02:19.439 --> 02:21.575 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the mayhem that occurred early
Sunday.

02:21.608 --> 02:25.579 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): As
soon as he entered
the club, he started firing and
he didn't

02:25.612 --> 02:26.580 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
stop.

02:26.613 --> 02:29.116 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He fired nonstop for 20 minutes
at least.

02:29.149 --> 02:32.219 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We thought that there were
several of them
because it just didn't stop.

02:32.252 --> 02:36.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The site is a
popular attraction
for tourists, and the majority
of the victims

02:36.990 --> 02:38.392 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
were foreign-born.

02:38.425 --> 02:43.530 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One American citizen was wounded
in the attack,
but returned home today.

02:43.563 --> 02:48.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was the latest in a string of
bloody incidents
and security lapses to take
place on Turkish

02:48.668 --> 02:50.003 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
soil.

02:50.037 --> 02:52.606 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Just two weeks ago, a gunman
assassinated
the Russian ambassador.

02:52.639 --> 02:59.513 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, in June, three suicide
bombers struck
Istanbul's Ataturk Airport,
killing 45 people.

02:59.546 --> 03:02.582 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That attack was also blamed on
ISIS.

03:02.616 --> 03:06.420 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the day's other news: The new
year is off
to a deadly start in Iraq.

03:06.453 --> 03:11.391 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A suicide bomber detonated a
truck bomb today
at a busy Baghdad market,
killing at least

03:11.425 --> 03:12.392 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
36 people.

03:12.426 --> 03:14.895 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Islamic State group claimed
responsibility.

03:14.928 --> 03:19.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The bomber pretended to be
looking to hire
day laborers and then set off
the explosion.

03:19.466 --> 03:22.135 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In addition to the dead, 52
people were wounded.

03:22.169 --> 03:26.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Later, appearing with the
visiting president
of France, Iraqi Prime Minister
Haider al-Abadi

03:26.973 --> 03:28.775 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
vowed to beat ISIS.

03:28.809 --> 03:32.612 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HAIDER AL-ABADI, Iraqi Prime
Minister (through
translator): I ask the security
forces and

03:32.646 --> 03:34.214 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the Iraqi people to be alert.

03:34.247 --> 03:36.316 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The terrorists are again
attacking civilians.

03:36.349 --> 03:40.153 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I promise the Iraqi people and
the French
president and all the countries
suffering

03:40.187 --> 03:43.523 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
attacks by the Islamic State
group that we
are fighting to finish them.

03:43.557 --> 03:47.794 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: This was the
third attack
claimed by ISIS in as many days
in and around

03:47.828 --> 03:49.629 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Baghdad.

03:49.663 --> 03:53.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sixty miles to the north, in
Samarra, gunmen
wearing suicide vests attacked
police stations

03:53.100 --> 03:56.236 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
late today, killing at least
seven officers.

03:56.269 --> 04:00.173 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Brazil, a riot at a prison
left at least
60 inmates dead.

04:00.207 --> 04:04.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There were chaotic scenes
outside the prison
in northern Amazonas state as
the killings

04:04.911 --> 04:06.279 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
erupted inside.

04:06.313 --> 04:10.083 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Authorities said several of the
inmates were
beheaded or dismembered.

04:10.117 --> 04:11.585 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Others escaped.

04:11.618 --> 04:15.722 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Officials blamed a fight between
members of
two crime gangs for the attacks.

04:15.755 --> 04:21.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Back in this country, 2016 ended
as one of
the most violent years ever in
Chicago.

04:21.228 --> 04:26.099 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The city saw 762 homicides, the
most in two
decades.

04:26.133 --> 04:29.102 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's more than New York and
Los Angeles
combined.

04:29.136 --> 04:34.741 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And there were 1,100 more
shooting incidents
in 2016 than the year before.

04:34.774 --> 04:38.578 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President-elect Trump tweeted
his reaction
to these numbers, saying: "If
mayor can't

04:38.612 --> 04:41.581 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
do it, he must ask for federal
help."

04:41.615 --> 04:45.785 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In another series of tweets, the
president-elect
also dismissed those who
questioned whether

04:45.819 --> 04:47.487 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
he'd win last fall.

04:47.521 --> 04:52.159 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Trump said he thought he'd
easily get more
than the 270 electoral votes
needed.

04:52.192 --> 04:54.027 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He ended up with 304.

04:54.060 --> 04:57.998 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hillary Clinton won the popular
vote by nearly
2.9 million.

04:58.031 --> 05:02.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also today, Trump spokesman Sean
Spicer played
down findings about Russian
hacking.

05:02.602 --> 05:07.207 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He told FOX News -- quote --
"There is zero
evidence that they influenced
the election."

05:07.240 --> 05:12.012 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
Turkey's
struggle to stop an onslaught of
terror attacks;

05:12.045 --> 05:18.318 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a new year and a new president,
looking ahead
to politics in 2017; plus,
looking back on

05:18.351 --> 05:28.395 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the president's effort to
conserve millions
of acres of land and water.

05:28.395 --> 05:33.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the president's effort to
conserve millions
of acres of land and water.

05:33.700 --> 05:37.571 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We return now to Turkey and this
weekend's
deadly attack in Istanbul.

05:37.604 --> 05:40.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What's behind that terror
incident and the
string of terror attacks in
Turkey that have

05:40.974 --> 05:43.577 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
taken place over there over the
past year?

05:43.610 --> 05:45.812 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We drill down on this with
Bulent Aliriza.

05:45.845 --> 05:50.183 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He directs the Turkey Project at
the Center
for Strategic and International
Studies.

05:50.217 --> 05:51.685 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Welcome.

05:51.718 --> 05:55.455 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ISIS has claimed responsibility
for this latest
attack on New Year's Eve.

05:55.488 --> 05:58.625 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Do you think the evidence will
point that
they're in fact the
perpetrators?

05:58.658 --> 06:02.162 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BULENT ALIRIZA, Center for
Strategic and International
Studies: Well, we do have a
statement by ISIS

06:02.195 --> 06:06.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
that, in fact, it was
responsible for this
outrage in Istanbul.

06:06.733 --> 06:11.271 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's actually the first time
that ISIS has
claimed responsibility for
terrorist acts

06:11.304 --> 06:16.576 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Turkey, although a number of
acts of terrorism
have been attributed to ISIS.

06:16.610 --> 06:22.882 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The method of operation by the
gunman -- apparently,
it was a single gunman involved
-- very much

06:22.916 --> 06:25.252 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
suggests that this was ISIS.

06:25.285 --> 06:29.155 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, as I said, there is a
statement by ISIS
that it did it.

06:29.189 --> 06:34.828 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, also, it's important to
note that, back
on November 2, soon after the
assault on Mosul

06:34.861 --> 06:41.101 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
began, Baghdadi, the leaders of
ISIS, made
a statement, part of which was
devoted to

06:41.134 --> 06:47.874 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Turkey, in which he asked his
followers to
move against Turkey because
Turkey had become,

06:47.907 --> 06:52.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as he called it, an apostate
state and, therefore,
attacks against Turkey were
warranted.

06:52.679 --> 06:56.416 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Turkey has
obviously been
suffering attacks not just from
ISIS, but

06:56.449 --> 06:58.418 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
also from Kurdish militant
groups.

06:58.451 --> 07:01.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For those people who haven't
been following
this closely, can you explain
this sort of

07:01.554 --> 07:03.290 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
two-front attack on Turkey?

07:03.323 --> 07:07.093 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BULENT ALIRIZA: Well, it's
exactly as you
put it, a two-front attack on
Turkey.

07:07.127 --> 07:12.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Turkey has been grappling with
Kurdish separatist
terrorism all the way back to
1984.

07:12.232 --> 07:17.237 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There have been efforts to
actually solve
the problem, the Kurdish problem
within Turkey.

07:17.270 --> 07:20.874 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But they essentially collapsed
in the middle
of 2015.

07:20.907 --> 07:27.947 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Since then, Turkey has been
reengaged in fighting
against the PKK, which is the
Kurdish separatist

07:27.981 --> 07:29.616 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
terrorist organization.

07:29.649 --> 07:32.585 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
More recently, it's been
challenged by ISIS.

07:32.619 --> 07:38.425 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, either of these challenges
would be daunting
for any state around the world.

07:38.458 --> 07:41.261 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The scourge of terrorism
bedevils the entire
world.

07:41.294 --> 07:46.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But for a country to have to
fight two very
potent terrorist organizations
within its

07:47.000 --> 07:52.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
borders, within its capital
city, within its
most important city, Istanbul,
the way that

07:52.272 --> 07:58.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it's been forced to during the
past 15, 18
months, is frankly very, very
difficult.

07:58.178 --> 08:01.981 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: How has
Erdogan been responding
to these attacks thus far?

08:02.015 --> 08:08.388 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BULENT ALIRIZA: Well, he and his
ministers
have been saying that the
security forces

08:08.421 --> 08:09.989 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
will eventually defeat
terrorism.

08:10.023 --> 08:13.293 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, that's a daunting task, as
I said, for
any state around the world.

08:13.326 --> 08:18.565 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Even the U.S. has not actually
-- with all
the effort that is made to deal
with terrorism,

08:18.598 --> 08:22.502 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not got to the position where it
says the
terrorist threat to the U.S. is
over.

08:22.535 --> 08:29.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, in Turkey's case, the fact
that it's
to the north of two ongoing
wars, in Syria

08:29.309 --> 08:36.049 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and Iraq, where some of the
terrorists who
are actually also intent on
harming Turkey

08:36.082 --> 08:40.420 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are active makes it so much more
difficult
for Turkey to try to solve the
problem within

08:40.453 --> 08:43.456 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
its borders, given the fact, as
I said, that
it comes from without.

08:43.490 --> 08:47.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: I mean,
Erdogan is also,
as we speak right now, going
through this

08:47.293 --> 08:52.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
very lengthy purge of officers
up and down
the government that he argues
were involved

08:52.332 --> 08:54.334 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in this recent coup attempt.

08:54.367 --> 08:58.204 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
How does that complicate their
fight against
terrorism within their own
borders?

08:58.238 --> 09:04.277 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BULENT ALIRIZA: Well, it
complicates it immensely,
because dealing with these two
threats was

09:04.310 --> 09:08.648 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
difficult enough, and then we
had a failed
coup attempt on July 15.

09:08.681 --> 09:14.454 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The government has moved against
the followers
of Fethullah Gulen that it
alleges were involved

09:14.487 --> 09:16.289 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
in this.

09:16.322 --> 09:19.592 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: This is the
religious figure
who is here in the U.S. that
Erdogan argues

09:19.626 --> 09:21.361 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
was behind the coup.

09:21.394 --> 09:25.064 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BULENT ALIRIZA: And the Turkish
government
has asked for his extradition,
and that has

09:25.098 --> 09:27.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
not happened so far.

09:27.400 --> 09:31.805 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's one of the reasons why
there is tension
between Ankara and Washington
currently.

09:31.838 --> 09:34.874 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Now, there has been a purge.

09:34.908 --> 09:41.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The attention of the government
has been directed
at rooting out of the system
those it believes

09:41.848 --> 09:47.587 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to be involved or are somehow
implicated or
are sympathetic to the coup.

09:47.620 --> 09:54.360 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And parallel to that, you have
the twin threats,
the unprecedented twin threats
from ISIS and

09:54.394 --> 09:58.565 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the PKK, and that is taxing the
capabilities
of the Turkish state.

09:58.598 --> 10:02.502 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Syria is also
involved in
these -- I'm sorry -- Turkey is
also involved

10:02.535 --> 10:05.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in some of the cease-fire that
has been going
on in Syria.

10:05.839 --> 10:10.109 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Is there any sense that you have
that, if
things were to calm down there
and the cease-fire

10:10.143 --> 10:13.713 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
were to really hold, that that
might ease
some of the pressure on Turkey?

10:13.746 --> 10:22.155 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BULENT ALIRIZA: Well, it could,
but the Turkish
