continue during president-elect
Trump's tenure.

22:43.696 --> 22:50.035 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tonight, we start with President
Obama's legacy
on conservation.

22:50.069 --> 22:54.573 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In his eight years in office,
President Obama
has permanently banned oil and
gas drilling

22:54.607 --> 23:00.012 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on hundreds of millions of acres
of federally
owned land in the Arctic and
Atlantic oceans.

23:00.045 --> 23:04.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's canceled oil and gas leases
on land owned
by the Blackfeet Nation in
Montana.

23:04.850 --> 23:09.788 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's also used his executive
power 29 times
to create new national
monuments, protecting

23:09.822 --> 23:13.892 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
more than 553 million acres of
water and land.

23:13.926 --> 23:17.930 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's more than the last 18
presidents combined.

23:17.963 --> 23:22.534 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In August, he more than
quadrupled the existing
marine national monument in the
Pacific Ocean

23:22.568 --> 23:25.971 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
near Hawaii, creating the
largest protected
area on Earth.

23:26.005 --> 23:31.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
Nature is actually resilient, if
we take care

23:32.011 --> 23:36.181 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to just stop actively destroying
it.

23:36.215 --> 23:41.453 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Last week, the
president
set aside two new national
monuments, Bears

23:41.487 --> 23:46.859 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Ears National Monument in Utah
and Gold Butte
National Monument in Nevada.

23:46.892 --> 23:50.396 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Environmentalists and Native
American groups
love the move, but critics have
called it

23:50.429 --> 23:54.099 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
an egregious and arrogant
federal land grab.

23:54.133 --> 23:58.704 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
With a new Republican Congress
and administration
coming in just a few weeks,
there are questions

23:58.737 --> 24:01.707 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about whether these efforts
might be rolled
back.

24:01.740 --> 24:05.778 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Last week, I talked with The
Washington Post's
Juliet Eilperin about Obama's
legacy.

24:05.811 --> 24:09.948 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I began by asking her about
the significance
of these two most recent
monuments.

24:09.982 --> 24:13.786 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JULIET EILPERIN, The Washington
Post: They're
both, for slightly different
reasons.

24:13.819 --> 24:16.121 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Gold Butte is an area.

24:16.155 --> 24:22.494 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's roughly 300,000 acres, just
about an
hour's drive from Las Vegas.

24:22.528 --> 24:28.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And it's got incredible
petrified sand dunes,
rock art.

24:28.033 --> 24:33.005 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a very important habitat
for the imperiled
desert tortoise.

24:33.038 --> 24:38.444 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And while it's this area where
people go to
hike and enjoy, it's also right
at the heart

24:38.477 --> 24:41.113 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of where Cliven Bundy and his
family live.

24:41.146 --> 24:44.383 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is a family that's been at
odds with
the federal government for
years.

24:44.416 --> 24:48.487 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: This is the
family that
was involved in the standoff in
2014 in Nevada

24:48.520 --> 24:50.356 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and then the other in Oregon.

24:50.389 --> 24:52.524 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JULIET EILPERIN: Exactly, and
then also the
occupation of the Malheur
National Wildlife

24:52.558 --> 24:54.326 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Refuge in Oregon.

24:54.360 --> 25:00.099 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so they have failed to
recognize federal
authority for over -- well over
a decade.

25:00.132 --> 25:02.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They have been illegally grazing
there.

25:02.034 --> 25:10.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so their property is right
adjacent to
this area that was declared a
national monument.

25:10.109 --> 25:12.344 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So it's quite an interesting
area for that
reason.

25:12.378 --> 25:17.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Bears Ears, in southeastern
Utah, which is
a larger parcel of land we're
talking about,

25:17.750 --> 25:24.390 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
1.35 million acres, is an
incredibly important
ancestral Pueblo site.

25:24.423 --> 25:25.391 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
And so...

25:25.424 --> 25:27.159 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: A Native
American site.

25:27.192 --> 25:29.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JULIET EILPERIN: So, it's a
Native American
site where there are many
tribes, some of

25:29.595 --> 25:33.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
