whom have
actually moved to other areas,
who consider

25:33.999 --> 25:37.569 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it an incredibly important and
significant
place.

25:37.603 --> 25:41.807 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
People still go there to collect
firewood
and collect herbs for
ceremonies.

25:41.840 --> 25:46.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They see it -- it has been a
literal refuge
over the years, as well as
obviously kind

25:46.912 --> 25:48.680 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of a spiritual refuge.

25:48.714 --> 25:50.048 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And so that's very important.

25:50.082 --> 25:52.451 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But there are real divisions
there.

25:52.484 --> 25:56.155 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
While a lot of people think it
should be protected,
there are real questions about,
again, the

25:56.188 --> 25:58.157 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
role of the federal government.

25:58.190 --> 26:02.127 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: So, these both
are considered
two of the more controversial of
Obama's designations,

26:02.161 --> 26:03.128 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
right?

26:03.162 --> 26:04.897 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JULIET EILPERIN: Absolutely.

26:04.930 --> 26:09.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Essentially, he spent many years
