26:17.876 --> 26:21.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: With regards
to the criticism,
particularly in Utah, there was
a lot of blowback

26:21.914 --> 26:23.682 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
there.

26:23.715 --> 26:26.819 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Orrin Hatch, both of the
senators, it seems
like every elected official in
Utah was against

26:26.852 --> 26:27.820 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
this.

26:27.853 --> 26:29.054 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JULIET EILPERIN: Right.

26:29.087 --> 26:30.222 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: What about the
criticisms
that they have?

26:30.255 --> 26:32.057 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What are they arguing that Obama
shouldn't
have done?

26:32.090 --> 26:36.829 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JULIET EILPERIN: What they were
arguing wasn't
that this area didn't deserve
protection,

26:36.862 --> 26:40.732 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
