32:24.943 --> 32:30.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JONATHAN SILVERS: For the past
15 years, Dafroza
Gauthier has risen at first
light to probe

32:30.182 --> 32:35.654 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Rwandan genocide and track
down fugitive
perpetrators, notably the
slaughter's architects

32:35.687 --> 32:38.190 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and executioners.

32:38.223 --> 32:43.428 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Gauthier was born and raised in
Rwanda and,
until recently, worked in the
chemical industry.

32:43.461 --> 32:46.765 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But she has become a formidable
war crimes
investigator, by necessity.

32:46.798 --> 32:50.936 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAFROZA GAUTHIER, War Crimes
Investigator
(through translator): We began
by collecting

32:50.969 --> 32:53.638 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
information and testimony from
our close friends
and families.

32:53.672 --> 32:57.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the more we heard their
stories, the more
we knew that something had to be
done.

32:57.876 --> 33:03.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JONATHAN SILVERS: Dafroza
Gauthier has only
one memento of her family, this
photo of her

33:03.481 --> 33:07.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mother, who was murdered along
with scores
of relatives in the spring of
1994.

33:07.986 --> 33:12.691 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Gauthier was living in Belgium
when the genocide
began, and she learned about her
family members'

33:12.724 --> 33:18.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
demise in real time, via a
series of phone
calls to her native village in
Rwanda.

33:18.830 --> 33:23.869 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The violence was rooted in
longstanding ethnic
division between the governing
Hutu majority

33:23.902 --> 33:25.670 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and the Tutsi minority.

33:25.704 --> 33:31.109 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the space of 100 days,
roughly 800,000
men, women, and children were
killed, mostly

33:31.142 --> 33:33.211 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ethnic Tutsi and moderate Hutus.

33:33.245 --> 33:37.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAFROZA GAUTHIER (through
translator): One
day, people should ask the
question why the

33:37.515 --> 33:39.618 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
world abandoned the Tutsis in
Rwanda.

33:39.651 --> 33:44.022 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are nation, states,
politicians who
should ask forgiveness of the
Rwandan people.

33:44.055 --> 33:48.293 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JONATHAN SILVERS: To date,
Gauthier and her
associates have tracked down
roughly 30 fugitive

33:48.326 --> 33:52.530 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
perpetrators of the genocide in
France and
its territories.

33:52.564 --> 33:57.569 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The dossiers on these
perpetrators, known
here in France as genocidaires,
grow larger

33:57.602 --> 33:59.237 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
by the week.

33:59.271 --> 34:04.175 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAFROZA GAUTHIER (through
translator): One
case can take two, three or four
years by

34:04.209 --> 34:06.211 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the time we collect the
evidence.

34:06.244 --> 34:11.149 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But what has to be denounced
today is why
is the public prosecutor is not
investigating.

34:11.182 --> 34:15.854 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Why is the public prosecutor
waiting for civil
plaintiffs like us to find the
evidence?

34:15.887 --> 34:18.657 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The public prosecutor should do
its job of
justice.

34:18.690 --> 34:20.392 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It shouldn't be our job.

34:20.425 --> 34:26.231 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JONATHAN SILVERS: The
investigative work is
a partnership, consecrated by 37
years of

34:26.264 --> 34:28.066 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
marriage.

34:28.099 --> 34:33.071 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Alain Gauthier met Dafroza in
Rwanda, where
Alain taught French in a foreign
aid program.

34:33.104 --> 34:38.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A native Frenchman and retired
high school
principal, he's learned to
navigate the bureaucracy

34:38.877 --> 34:40.845 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that is the French legal system.

34:40.879 --> 34:46.685 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Together, he and wife
established an organization,
the Civil Parties Collective for
Rwanda, to

34:46.718 --> 34:49.921 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
secure legal status as
plaintiffs in civil
suits.

34:49.955 --> 34:52.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALAIN GAUTHIER, War Crimes
Investigator (through
translator): We were forced to
investigate

34:52.991 --> 34:56.428 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ourselves, because the public
prosecutor never
pressed charges.

34:56.461 --> 35:00.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
All the cases concerning the
murder of Tutsis
in Rwanda came solely through
the will of

35:00.298 --> 35:02.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the plaintiffs.

35:02.167 --> 35:06.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JONATHAN SILVERS: After years of
legal wrangling,
a senior figure in the Rwandan
genocide faced

35:06.471 --> 35:11.176 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
French justice for the first
time in February
2014.

35:11.209 --> 35:15.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Gauthiers have filed a civil
action that
led the justice ministry to
prosecute the

35:15.880 --> 35:19.951 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
defendant, Pascal Simbikangwa.

35:19.985 --> 35:24.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Simbikangwa held a senior
position in the
Rwandan state security service
in the 1990s.

35:24.756 --> 35:29.060 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Despite being paralyzed from the
waste down
during the genocide, he helped
arm the Hutu

35:29.094 --> 35:34.299 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
militia and organized roadblocks
where thousands
of fleeing Tutsi were murdered.

35:34.332 --> 35:38.970 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Gauthiers found him living
under an assumed
name in the French territory of
Mayotte in

35:39.004 --> 35:40.605 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the Indian Ocean.

35:40.638 --> 35:45.310 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He'd fled there after the
genocide and survived
by forging identity documents.

35:45.343 --> 35:47.512 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
French authorities arrested him
in 2008.

35:47.545 --> 35:52.917 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ALAIN GAUTHIER (through
translator): In some
cases, we had to travel three,
four or five

35:52.951 --> 35:56.121 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
times to Rwanda to take as much
testimony
as possible.

35:56.154 --> 35:58.957 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Then, all that testimony had to
be translated.

35:58.990 --> 36:03.028 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The testimony has to be
organized and given
to our lawyers to draft a
complaint.

36:03.061 --> 36:05.463 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Every case requires a large
amount of work.

36:05.497 --> 36:09.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's hard for plaintiffs like
us, who are
not trained for this type of
work.

36:09.501 --> 36:15.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JONATHAN SILVERS: The Gauthiers'
pursuit of
fugitive perpetrators has forced
France to

36:15.040 --> 36:18.877 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
examine its conduct both during
and after
the genocide.

36:18.910 --> 36:23.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
France had close relations with
the Hutu-led
regime that carried out the
slaughter.

36:23.481 --> 36:28.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the aftermath, Rwanda's
post-genocide government
has accused France of
complicity, obstructing

36:28.620 --> 36:32.223 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the escape of Hutu killers, and
harboring
fugitives.

36:32.257 --> 36:37.295 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Most recently, the European
Human Rights Court
condemned France for excessive
delays in investigating

36:37.328 --> 36:39.564 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
