studies.

36:52.177 --> 36:58.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARCEL KABANDA, Historian
(through translator):
For 20 years, we asked ourselves
if France

36:58.850 --> 37:02.487 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
wasn't becoming a paradise for
Rwandan war
criminals.

37:02.520 --> 37:06.858 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
France must not be the country
that gives
impunity to the killers behind
the genocide.

37:06.891 --> 37:14.065 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JONATHAN SILVERS: The effort to
bring Rwanda
